{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2366,"text":"(Nature sounds)"},{"time":7820,"text":"When I first began\nrecording wild soundscapes"},{"time":10536,"text":"45 years ago,"},{"time":12467,"text":"I had no idea that ants,"},{"time":14889,"text":"insect larvae, sea anemones and viruses"},{"time":18368,"text":"created a sound signature."},{"time":20496,"text":"But they do."},{"time":21939,"text":"And so does every wild\nhabitat on the planet,"},{"time":25352,"text":"like the Amazon rainforest\nyou're hearing behind me."},{"time":28587,"text":"In fact, temperate\nand tropical rainforests"},{"time":32161,"text":"each produce a vibrant animal orchestra,"},{"time":35341,"text":"that instantaneous\nand organized expression"},{"time":38569,"text":"of insects, reptiles,\namphibians, birds and mammals."},{"time":43377,"text":"And every soundscape\nthat springs from a wild habitat"},{"time":46304,"text":"generates its own unique signature,"},{"time":49896,"text":"one that contains incredible\namounts of information,"},{"time":52813,"text":"and it's some of that information\nI want to share with you today."},{"time":57172,"text":"The soundscape is made\nup of three basic sources."},{"time":60378,"text":"The first is the geophony,"},{"time":62917,"text":"or the nonbiological sounds that occur"},{"time":65283,"text":"in any given habitat,"},{"time":67260,"text":"like wind in the trees, water in a stream,"},{"time":69852,"text":"waves at the ocean shore,\nmovement of the Earth."},{"time":73446,"text":"The second of these is the biophony."},{"time":76724,"text":"The biophony is all of the sound"},{"time":79846,"text":"that's generated by organisms\nin a given habitat"},{"time":82964,"text":"at one time and in one place."},{"time":86584,"text":"And the third is all of the sound\nthat we humans generate"},{"time":91118,"text":"that's called anthrophony."},{"time":92936,"text":"Some of it is controlled,\nlike music or theater,"},{"time":96297,"text":"but most of it is chaotic and incoherent,"},{"time":100214,"text":"which some of us refer to as noise."},{"time":103919,"text":"There was a time when\nI considered wild soundscapes"},{"time":106619,"text":"to be a worthless artifact."},{"time":108351,"text":"They were just there,\nbut they had no significance."},{"time":112433,"text":"Well, I was wrong. What\nI learned from these encounters"},{"time":115806,"text":"was that careful listening gives\nus incredibly valuable tools"},{"time":120582,"text":"by which to evaluate\nthe health of a habitat"},{"time":123166,"text":"across the entire spectrum of life."},{"time":126978,"text":"When I began recording in the late '60s,"},{"time":130190,"text":"the typical methods\nof recording were limited"},{"time":133466,"text":"to the fragmented capture\nof individual species"},{"time":137934,"text":"like birds mostly, in the beginning,"},{"time":141030,"text":"but later animals\nlike mammals and amphibians."},{"time":146731,"text":"To me, this was a little like trying\nto understand"},{"time":150243,"text":"the magnificence\nof Beethoven's Fifth Symphony"},{"time":153308,"text":"by abstracting the sound\nof a single violin player"},{"time":156217,"text":"out of the context of the orchestra"},{"time":158787,"text":"and hearing just that one part."},{"time":161890,"text":"Fortunately, more and more institutions"},{"time":164907,"text":"are implementing the more holistic models"},{"time":166975,"text":"that I and a few of my colleagues\nhave introduced"},{"time":169338,"text":"to the field of soundscape ecology."},{"time":173211,"text":"When I began recording\nover four decades ago,"},{"time":178279,"text":"I could record for 10 hours"},{"time":180688,"text":"and capture one hour of usable material,"},{"time":182923,"text":"good enough for an album\nor a film soundtrack"},{"time":185980,"text":"or a museum installation."},{"time":188699,"text":"Now, because of global warming,"},{"time":191652,"text":"resource extraction,"},{"time":193070,"text":"and human noise, among many other factors,"},{"time":196139,"text":"it can take up to 1,000 hours or more"},{"time":198815,"text":"to capture the same thing."},{"time":201648,"text":"Fully 50 percent of my archive"},{"time":204703,"text":"comes from habitats so radically altered"},{"time":207899,"text":"that they're either altogether silent"},{"time":210799,"text":"or can no longer be heard\nin any of their original form."},{"time":215520,"text":"The usual methods of evaluating a habitat"},{"time":217806,"text":"have been done by visually\ncounting the numbers of species"},{"time":221132,"text":"and the numbers of individuals\nwithin each species in a given area."},{"time":225337,"text":"However, by comparing\ndata that ties together"},{"time":228889,"text":"both density and diversity\nfrom what we hear,"},{"time":231689,"text":"I'm able to arrive at much\nmore precise fitness outcomes."},{"time":237062,"text":"And I want to show you some examples"},{"time":239102,"text":"that typify the possibilities unlocked"},{"time":241892,"text":"by diving into this universe."},{"time":244914,"text":"This is Lincoln Meadow."},{"time":246306,"text":"Lincoln\nMeadow's a three-and-a-half-hour drive"},{"time":248521,"text":"east of San Francisco\nin the Sierra Nevada Mountains,"},{"time":251414,"text":"at about 2,000 meters altitude,"},{"time":253511,"text":"and I've been recording\nthere for many years."},{"time":256320,"text":"In 1988, a logging company\nconvinced local residents"},{"time":260240,"text":"that there would be absolutely\nno environmental impact"},{"time":263402,"text":"from a new method they were trying"},{"time":265046,"text":"called \"selective logging,\""},{"time":266766,"text":"taking out a tree here and there"},{"time":268321,"text":"rather than clear-cutting a whole area."},{"time":271604,"text":"With permission granted to record"},{"time":273364,"text":"both before and after the operation,"},{"time":275327,"text":"I set up my gear and captured\na large number of dawn choruses"},{"time":279945,"text":"to very strict protocol\nand calibrated recordings,"},{"time":283478,"text":"because I wanted a really good baseline."},{"time":285672,"text":"This is an example of a spectrogram."},{"time":287857,"text":"A spectrogram is a graphic\nillustration of sound"},{"time":290288,"text":"with time from left\nto right across the page --"},{"time":293461,"text":"15 seconds in this case is represented â€”"},{"time":295968,"text":"and frequency from the bottom\nof the page to the top,"},{"time":298823,"text":"lowest to highest."},{"time":300042,"text":"And you can see\nthat the signature of a stream"},{"time":303176,"text":"is represented here in the bottom\nthird or half of the page,"},{"time":307981,"text":"while birds that were once in that meadow"},{"time":311424,"text":"are represented in the signature\nacross the top."},{"time":314481,"text":"There were a lot of them."},{"time":315636,"text":"And here's Lincoln Meadow\nbefore selective logging."},{"time":318800,"text":"(Nature sounds)"},{"time":333593,"text":"Well, a year later I returned,"},{"time":335471,"text":"and using the same protocols"},{"time":337228,"text":"and recording under the same conditions,"},{"time":339943,"text":"I recorded a number of examples"},{"time":342171,"text":"of the same dawn choruses,"},{"time":344271,"text":"and now this is what we've got."},{"time":346414,"text":"This is after selective logging."},{"time":347694,"text":"You can see that the stream\nis still represented"},{"time":350004,"text":"in the bottom third of the page,"},{"time":351674,"text":"but notice what's missing\nin the top two thirds."},{"time":356177,"text":"(Nature sounds)"},{"time":361690,"text":"Coming up is the sound of a woodpecker."},{"time":371177,"text":"Well, I've returned\nto Lincoln Meadow 15 times"},{"time":373767,"text":"in the last 25 years,"},{"time":375251,"text":"and I can tell you that the biophony,"},{"time":378937,"text":"the density and diversity\nof that biophony,"},{"time":381842,"text":"has not yet returned\nto anything like it was"},{"time":384394,"text":"before the operation."},{"time":386592,"text":"But here's a picture\nof Lincoln Meadow taken after,"},{"time":389690,"text":"and you can see\nthat from the perspective of the camera"},{"time":392928,"text":"or the human eye,"},{"time":394039,"text":"hardly a stick or a tree\nappears to be out of place,"},{"time":396814,"text":"which would confirm the logging\ncompany's contention"},{"time":399754,"text":"that there's nothing\nof environmental impact."},{"time":402383,"text":"However, our ears tell us\na very different story."},{"time":408800,"text":"Young students are always asking me"},{"time":410627,"text":"what these animals are saying,"},{"time":412080,"text":"and really I've got no idea."},{"time":416911,"text":"But I can tell you that they do\nexpress themselves."},{"time":422180,"text":"Whether or not we understand\nit is a different story."},{"time":425258,"text":"I was walking along the shore in Alaska,"},{"time":427586,"text":"and I came across this tide pool"},{"time":429930,"text":"filled with a colony of sea anemones,"},{"time":432962,"text":"these wonderful eating machines,"},{"time":435038,"text":"relatives of coral and jellyfish."},{"time":437889,"text":"And curious to see\nif any of them made any noise,"},{"time":440247,"text":"I dropped a hydrophone,"},{"time":441418,"text":"an underwater microphone\ncovered in rubber,"},{"time":444410,"text":"down the mouth part,"},{"time":445598,"text":"and immediately the critter began"},{"time":447359,"text":"to absorb the microphone into its belly,"},{"time":449568,"text":"and the tentacles were\nsearching out of the surface"},{"time":452262,"text":"for something of nutritional value."},{"time":454673,"text":"The static-like sounds that are very low,"},{"time":457178,"text":"that you're going to hear right now."},{"time":459182,"text":"(Static sounds)"},{"time":463584,"text":"Yeah, but watch. When it\ndidn't find anything to eat --"},{"time":466451,"text":"(Honking sound)"},{"time":467840,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":470500,"text":"I think that's an expression\nthat can be understood"},{"time":472997,"text":"in any language."},{"time":474414,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":479280,"text":"At the end of its breeding cycle,"},{"time":480880,"text":"the Great Basin Spadefoot toad"},{"time":483036,"text":"digs itself down about a meter under"},{"time":485111,"text":"the hard-panned desert\nsoil of the American West,"},{"time":488261,"text":"where it can stay for many seasons"},{"time":490140,"text":"until conditions are just\nright for it to emerge again."},{"time":493640,"text":"And when there's enough moisture\nin the soil"},{"time":495760,"text":"in the spring, frogs will dig\nthemselves to the surface"},{"time":498555,"text":"and gather around these\nlarge, vernal pools"},{"time":502626,"text":"in great numbers."},{"time":504663,"text":"And they vocalize in a chorus"},{"time":508069,"text":"that's absolutely in sync\nwith one another."},{"time":511277,"text":"And they do that for two reasons."},{"time":512873,"text":"The first is competitive,\nbecause they're looking for mates,"},{"time":516302,"text":"and the second is cooperative,"},{"time":517755,"text":"because if they're\nall vocalizing in sync together,"},{"time":520236,"text":"it makes it really difficult\nfor predators like coyotes,"},{"time":524395,"text":"foxes and owls to single\nout any individual for a meal."},{"time":528614,"text":"This is a spectrogram\nof what the frog chorusing looks like"},{"time":531886,"text":"when it's in a very healthy pattern."},{"time":534147,"text":"(Frogs croaking)"},{"time":544163,"text":"Mono Lake is just to the east\nof Yosemite National Park"},{"time":548128,"text":"in California,"},{"time":549957,"text":"and it's a favorite\nhabitat of these toads,"},{"time":552812,"text":"and it's also favored by U.S.\nNavy jet pilots,"},{"time":555699,"text":"who train in their fighters\nflying them at speeds"},{"time":558745,"text":"exceeding 1,100 kilometers an hour"},{"time":561203,"text":"and altitudes only a couple hundred meters"},{"time":563984,"text":"above ground level of the Mono Basin,"},{"time":566563,"text":"very fast, very low, and so loud"},{"time":570237,"text":"that the anthrophony, the human noise,"},{"time":573103,"text":"even though it's six and a half kilometers"},{"time":575127,"text":"from the frog pond you\njust heard a second ago,"},{"time":577927,"text":"it masked the sound\nof the chorusing toads."},{"time":581493,"text":"You can see in this spectrogram\nthat all of the energy"},{"time":584759,"text":"that was once in the first\nspectrogram is gone"},{"time":587506,"text":"from the top end of the spectrogram,"},{"time":589253,"text":"and that there's breaks\nin the chorusing at two and a half,"},{"time":592087,"text":"four and a half,\nand six and a half seconds,"},{"time":594279,"text":"and then the sound\nof the jet, the signature,"},{"time":597378,"text":"is in yellow at the very\nbottom of the page."},{"time":599937,"text":"(Frogs croaking)"},{"time":609582,"text":"Now at the end of that flyby,"},{"time":611976,"text":"it took the frogs fully 45 minutes"},{"time":615465,"text":"to regain their chorusing synchronicity,"},{"time":617869,"text":"during which time, and under a full moon,"},{"time":620814,"text":"we watched as two coyotes\nand a great horned owl"},{"time":623595,"text":"came in to pick\noff a few of their numbers."},{"time":626718,"text":"The good news is that, with a little bit\nof habitat restoration"},{"time":630244,"text":"and fewer flights, the frog populations,"},{"time":632949,"text":"once diminishing\nduring the 1980s and early '90s,"},{"time":636672,"text":"have pretty much returned to normal."},{"time":640205,"text":"I want to end with a story\ntold by a beaver."},{"time":643144,"text":"It's a very sad story,"},{"time":644618,"text":"but it really illustrates how animals"},{"time":648496,"text":"can sometimes show emotion,"},{"time":650478,"text":"a very controversial subject\namong some older biologists."},{"time":655130,"text":"A colleague of mine was recording\nin the American Midwest"},{"time":658363,"text":"around this pond that had been formed"},{"time":660905,"text":"maybe 16,000 years ago at the end\nof the last ice age."},{"time":664804,"text":"It was also formed in part by a beaver dam"},{"time":666957,"text":"at one end that held\nthat whole ecosystem together"},{"time":669875,"text":"in a very delicate balance."},{"time":672627,"text":"And one afternoon, while he was recording,"},{"time":676402,"text":"there suddenly appeared\nfrom out of nowhere"},{"time":680226,"text":"a couple of game wardens,"},{"time":682674,"text":"who for no apparent reason,"},{"time":684269,"text":"walked over to the beaver dam,"},{"time":685848,"text":"dropped a stick of dynamite\ndown it, blowing it up,"},{"time":689130,"text":"killing the female and her young babies."},{"time":693160,"text":"Horrified, my colleagues remained behind"},{"time":695992,"text":"to gather his thoughts"},{"time":698033,"text":"and to record whatever he could\nthe rest of the afternoon,"},{"time":701517,"text":"and that evening, he captured\na remarkable event:"},{"time":706410,"text":"the lone surviving male beaver\nswimming in slow circles"},{"time":710599,"text":"crying out inconsolably for its\nlost mate and offspring."},{"time":716332,"text":"This is probably the saddest sound"},{"time":719241,"text":"I've ever heard coming from any organism,"},{"time":722159,"text":"human or other."},{"time":726517,"text":"(Beaver crying)"},{"time":742180,"text":"Yeah. Well."},{"time":743995,"text":"There are many facets to soundscapes,"},{"time":746577,"text":"among them the ways in which animals\ntaught us to dance and sing,"},{"time":749793,"text":"which I'll save for another time."},{"time":752418,"text":"But you have heard how biophonies"},{"time":755436,"text":"help clarify our understanding\nof the natural world."},{"time":759279,"text":"You've heard the impact\nof resource extraction,"},{"time":761743,"text":"human noise and habitat destruction."},{"time":764807,"text":"And where environmental\nsciences have typically"},{"time":767070,"text":"tried to understand\nthe world from what we see,"},{"time":770127,"text":"a much fuller understanding\ncan be got from what we hear."},{"time":774595,"text":"Biophonies and geophonies\nare the signature voices"},{"time":778452,"text":"of the natural world,"},{"time":780443,"text":"and as we hear them,"},{"time":781796,"text":"we're endowed with a sense of place,"},{"time":784468,"text":"the true story of the world we live in."},{"time":787885,"text":"In a matter of seconds,"},{"time":789804,"text":"a soundscape reveals much more information"},{"time":792519,"text":"from many perspectives,"},{"time":794067,"text":"from quantifiable data\nto cultural inspiration."},{"time":798689,"text":"Visual capture implicitly frames"},{"time":801590,"text":"a limited frontal perspective\nof a given spatial context,"},{"time":805586,"text":"while soundscapes widen that scope"},{"time":807959,"text":"to a full 360 degrees,\ncompletely enveloping us."},{"time":813144,"text":"And while a picture may\nbe worth 1,000 words,"},{"time":816916,"text":"a soundscape is worth 1,000 pictures."},{"time":821289,"text":"And our ears tell us"},{"time":823413,"text":"that the whisper\nof every leaf and creature"},{"time":827008,"text":"speaks to the natural\nsources of our lives,"},{"time":830082,"text":"which indeed may hold the secrets\nof love for all things,"},{"time":835144,"text":"especially our own humanity,"},{"time":837102,"text":"and the last word goes\nto a jaguar from the Amazon."},{"time":843387,"text":"(Growling)"},{"time":857135,"text":"Thank you for listening."},{"time":859335,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}